#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.69"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.69:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.69:0.2"
msgid "7. Devatāvagga"
msgstr "7. A God"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.69:0.3"
msgid "69. Devatāsutta"
msgstr "69. A God"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.69:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ "
"jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then, late at night, a glorious deity, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, "
"went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "an6.69:1.2"
msgid "“chayime, bhante, dhammā bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr "“Sir, these six things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant."

msgctxt "an6.69:1.3"
msgid "Katame cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.69:1.4"
msgid ""
"Satthugāravatā, dhammagāravatā, saṅghagāravatā, sikkhāgāravatā, sovacassatā, "
"kalyāṇamittatā—"
msgstr ""
"Respect for the Teacher, for the teaching, for the Saṅgha, for the training; "
"being easy to admonish, and good friendship."

msgctxt "an6.69:1.5"
msgid "ime kho, bhante, cha dhammā bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr "These six things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant.”"

msgctxt "an6.69:1.6"
msgid "Idamavoca sā devatā."
msgstr "That’s what that deity said,"

msgctxt "an6.69:1.7"
msgid "Samanuñño satthā ahosi."
msgstr "and the teacher approved."

msgctxt "an6.69:1.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā devatā “samanuñño me satthā”ti bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā "
"padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi."
msgstr ""
"Then that deity, knowing that the teacher approved, bowed, and respectfully "
"circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before vanishing right there."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.424"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.69:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then, when the night had passed, the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.69:2.2"
msgid ""
"“imaṃ, bhikkhave, rattiṃ aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā "
"abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, "
"bhikkhave, sā devatā maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"“Tonight, a glorious deity, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, came to me, "
"bowed, stood to one side, and said to me:"

msgctxt "an6.69:2.3"
msgid "‘chayime, bhante, dhammā bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr "‘Sir, these six things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant."

msgctxt "an6.69:2.4"
msgid "Katame cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.69:2.5"
msgid ""
"Satthugāravatā, dhammagāravatā, saṅghagāravatā, sikkhāgāravatā, sovacassatā, "
"kalyāṇamittatā—"
msgstr ""
"Respect for the Teacher, for the teaching, for the Saṅgha, for the training; "
"being easy to admonish, and good friendship."

msgctxt "an6.69:2.6"
msgid "ime kho, bhante, cha dhammā bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattantī’ti."
msgstr "These six things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant.’"

msgctxt "an6.69:2.7"
msgid "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, sā devatā."
msgstr "That is what that deity said."

msgctxt "an6.69:2.8"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Then he bowed and respectfully circled me, keeping me on his right side, "
"before vanishing right there.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.69:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Sāriputta said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an6.69:3.2"
msgid ""
"“imassa kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena "
"atthaṃ ājānāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, this is how I understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief "
"statement."

msgctxt "an6.69:3.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhante, bhikkhu attanā ca satthugāravo hoti satthugāravatāya ca "
"vaṇṇavādī."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant personally respects the Teacher and praises such "
"respect."

msgctxt "an6.69:3.4"
msgid "Ye caññe bhikkhū na satthugāravā te ca satthugāravatāya samādapeti."
msgstr ""
"And they encourage other mendicants who lack such respect to respect the "
"Teacher."

msgctxt "an6.69:3.5"
msgid ""
"Ye caññe bhikkhū satthugāravā tesañca vaṇṇaṃ bhaṇati bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena."
msgstr ""
"And they praise other mendicants who respect the Teacher at the right time, "
"truthfully and substantively."

msgctxt "an6.69:3.6"
msgid "Attanā ca dhammagāravo hoti …"
msgstr "They personally respect the teaching …"

msgctxt "an6.69:3.7"
msgid "saṅghagāravo hoti …"
msgstr "They personally respect the Saṅgha …"

msgctxt "an6.69:3.8"
msgid "sikkhāgāravo hoti …"
msgstr "They personally respect the training …"

msgctxt "an6.69:3.9"
msgid "suvaco hoti …"
msgstr "They are personally easy to admonish …"

msgctxt "an6.69:3.10"
msgid "kalyāṇamitto hoti kalyāṇamittatāya ca vaṇṇavādī."
msgstr "They personally have good friends, and praise such friendship."

msgctxt "an6.69:3.11"
msgid "Ye caññe bhikkhū na kalyāṇamittā te ca kalyāṇamittatāya samādapeti."
msgstr ""
"And they encourage other mendicants who lack good friends to develop good "
"friendship."

msgctxt "an6.69:3.12"
msgid ""
"Ye caññe bhikkhū kalyāṇamittā tesañca vaṇṇaṃ bhaṇati bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena."
msgstr ""
"And they praise other mendicants who have good friends at the right time, "
"truthfully and substantively."

msgctxt "an6.69:3.13"
msgid ""
"Imassa kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena "
"atthaṃ ājānāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how I understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief "
"statement.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.425"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.69:4.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta."
msgstr "“Good, good, Sāriputta!"

msgctxt "an6.69:4.2"
msgid ""
"Sādhu kho tvaṃ, sāriputta, imassa mayā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ "
"vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāsi."
msgstr ""
"It’s good that you understand the detailed meaning of what I’ve said in "
"brief like this."

msgctxt "an6.69:4.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, sāriputta, bhikkhu attanā ca satthugāravo hoti satthugāravatāya ca "
"vaṇṇavādī."
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant personally respects the Teacher …"

msgctxt "an6.69:4.4"
msgid "Ye caññe bhikkhū na satthugāravā te ca satthugāravatāya samādapeti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.69:4.5"
msgid ""
"Ye caññe bhikkhū satthugāravā tesañca vaṇṇaṃ bhaṇati bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.69:4.6"
msgid "Attanā ca dhammagāravo hoti …"
msgstr "They personally respect the teaching …"

msgctxt "an6.69:4.7"
msgid "saṅghagāravo hoti …"
msgstr "They personally respect the Saṅgha …"

msgctxt "an6.69:4.8"
msgid "sikkhāgāravo hoti …"
msgstr "They personally respect the training …"

msgctxt "an6.69:4.9"
msgid "suvaco hoti …"
msgstr "They are personally easy to admonish …"

msgctxt "an6.69:4.10"
msgid "kalyāṇamitto hoti kalyāṇamittatāya ca vaṇṇavādī."
msgstr "They personally have good friends, and praise such friendship."

msgctxt "an6.69:4.11"
msgid "Ye caññe bhikkhū na kalyāṇamittā te ca kalyāṇamittatāya samādapeti."
msgstr ""
"And they encourage other mendicants who lack good friends to develop good "
"friendship."

msgctxt "an6.69:4.12"
msgid ""
"Ye caññe bhikkhū kalyāṇamittā tesañca vaṇṇaṃ bhaṇati bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ kālena."
msgstr ""
"And they praise other mendicants who have good friends at the right time, "
"truthfully and substantively."

msgctxt "an6.69:4.13"
msgid ""
"Imassa kho, sāriputta, mayā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena attho "
"daṭṭhabbo”ti."
msgstr ""
"This is how to understand the detailed meaning of what I said in brief.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.69:4.14"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
